-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Banco do Brasil, Ecorodovias and Hering
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-06-26T21:09:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/brazilian-stock-movers-banco-do-brasil-ccx-carvao-ecorodovias.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the market close. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index rose 0.1 percent to 53,836.57.  Banco do Brasil SA  (BBAS3 BS) fell 2.4 percent to 18.65
reais, the lowest level in three years. The lender and
Votorantim Financas SA will inject 1 billion reais ($482
million) each in Banco Votorantim SA, Banco do Brasil said in a
regulatory filing yesterday after the market closed.  Ecorodovias Infraestrutura e Logistica SA  (ECOR3 BS)
declined 2.3 percent to 16.11 reais. The road concession group
said in a regulatory filing today that a shareholder, Primav
Construcoes e Comercio SA, plans to pay 16.59 reais a share to
buy an additional 19 percent stake in the company from Impregilo
International Infrastructures NV in a 1.76 billion reais deal.  Cia. Hering (HGTX3)  (HGTX3 BS),  Brazil ’s second-biggest clothing
retailer, slumped 7.7 percent to 37.06 reais, the most in nine
months, on mounting concern a deeper global slowdown will curb
growth in the country and affect the company’s results.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denyse Godoy in Sao Paulo at 
